BLOCK INFO HEADER

This block defines the modes and states for the equipment module. If the EM is linked to the unit, the unit status is fully applied to the EM and a manual/direct EM control is not possible. If the EM is not linked to the unit, the operator can set the mode and state manually, enable simulation and disable alarms. However, the Acknowledge commands and SafetyReleased are still taken from the unit. Acknowledge and SafetyReleased from the unit are always applied, independently from being linked or not. If controlled directly, the local interface has priority over the hmi interface
